# Environment Variables Template
# 
# Copy this file to .env for local development:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# SECURITY WARNING: 
# - NEVER commit the .env file to git
# - The .env file is already in .gitignore
# - For production, set these in Vercel's Environment Variables settings

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CONFIGURATION (FRONTEND)
# =============================================================================

# Your Supabase project URL
# Find this in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API
# Example: https://abcdefghijklmnop.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co

# Your Supabase anon/public key
# Find this in: Supabase Dashboard → Project Settings → API → Project API keys → anon/public
# This is safe to use in client-side code (it's called "anon" key for a reason)
VITE_SUPABASE_KEY=your-anon-key-here

# =============================================================================
# SUPABASE CLI CONFIGURATION (OPTIONAL - for backend/functions development)
# =============================================================================

# Supabase Project Reference (for CLI commands)
# Example: frwawmcvrpdhsuljrvlw
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=your_project_ref_here

# Supabase Access Token (for CLI authentication)
# Generate at: https://supabase.com/dashboard/account/tokens
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here

# =============================================================================
# VERCEL DEPLOYMENT INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================
#
# To deploy to Vercel with these environment variables:
#
# 1. Go to your Vercel project dashboard
# 2. Navigate to: Settings → Environment Variables
# 3. Add these variables:
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_URL (set value from Supabase dashboard)
#    - VITE_SUPABASE_KEY (set value from Supabase dashboard)
# 4. Make sure to set them for all environments (Production, Preview, Development)
# 5. Redeploy your application
#
# The build process will automatically replace placeholders with these values.
#
# =============================================================================
# SECURITY BEST PRACTICES
# =============================================================================
#
# ✅ DO:
#   - Keep the .env file in .gitignore (already configured)
#   - Use different Supabase projects for dev/staging/production
#   - Rotate keys if they are ever exposed
#   - Use Supabase RLS (Row Level Security) policies
#   - Set appropriate CORS policies in Supabase
#
# ❌ DON'T:
#   - Never commit .env or .env.local files
#   - Never share your .env file in chat/email
#   - Never use production keys in development
#   - Never expose the service_role key (only use anon key in frontend)
#   - Never disable RLS without a very good reason
#
# =============================================================================
# NOTES
# =============================================================================
#
# - The VITE_ prefix is used for compatibility with Vite-based tooling
# - These variables are replaced at BUILD time, not runtime
# - Changes to these variables require a rebuild/redeploy
# - Local development uses the .env file
# - Vercel deployment uses Environment Variables from dashboard
#
